  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink237-kilavi">allakuṟippaṭṭu nīṅkiya talaimakaṉai vantilaṉākakkoṇṭu avaṉ piṉpu vantuḻi avaṟkut tōḻi colliyatu.  </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> What the confidante told the hero who came later,
          having taken (i.e., misunderstood) him who had left, being misled by a false sign,
          as one who had not come.
          
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink237">
<l>kāmaṅ kaṭava vuḷḷa miṉaippa</l>
<l>yāmvantu kāṇpatōr paruva māyi</l>
<l>ṉōṅkit tōṉṟu muyarvaraik</l>
<l>kiyāṅkeṉap paṭuvatu nummūr teyyō</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>As desire incites and the heart torments,</l>
        <l>if there [comes] a season for us to come and see [you],</l>
        <l>where is your town said to be,</l>
        <l>[in relation] to the high mountain that appears lofty?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
